# X2G-Agent

X2G-Agent is an agentic workflow library for coordinating end-use energy simulation and power-grid simulation.

The first implemented case study is **Building-to-Grid**: a single-building EnergyPlus load profile is standardized, mapped to an OpenDSS bus, injected into a simple radial feeder, evaluated, and reported.

## Quick Start

```powershell
python -m pip install -e ".[dev]"
python scripts/run_building_to_grid.py --config configs/building_to_grid.yaml
pytest
```

The default configuration runs in mock mode, so it does not require EnergyPlus or OpenDSS to be installed. Outputs are written under `outputs/building_to_grid/`.

## External Simulators

EnergyPlus executable, IDF, and EPW paths are read from `configs/building_to_grid.yaml` or from `.env` variables:

```text
ENERGYPLUS_EXE=C:\EnergyPlusV24-1-0\energyplus.exe
ENERGYPLUS_IDF=D:\models\building.idf
ENERGYPLUS_EPW=D:\weather\site.epw
```

OpenDSSDirect.py is used by `x2g_agent.tools.opendss` when `opendss.mode` is set to `direct`.

## Package Layout

- `src/x2g_agent/agents/`: workflow agents
- `src/x2g_agent/tools/`: wrappers for external simulator calls
- `configs/building_to_grid.yaml`: runnable case-study config
- `data_sample/opendss/`: simple sample radial feeder
- `docs/cases/building_to_grid.md`: case-study documentation
- `tests/`: pytest coverage for mock mode
